Key aspects of students include:
Educational Context: In many countries (e.g., UK), "student" refers to
those in secondary school or higher, while younger learners are "pupils".
In the US, it applies to all school attendees.
Active Learning: Beyond formal schooling, a student can be anyone who studies 
or investigates a subject, such as a "student of human nature".
Types: This includes undergraduate, graduate, postgraduate, part-time, and full-time learners.
